                <h1>Michael Phelps: The Olympic Legend Who Changed Swimming Forever</h1>
                <p>Michael Phelps, the most decorated Olympian of all time, has redefined swimming with his unparalleled achievements. Born on June 30, 1985, in Baltimore, Maryland, he holds 23 Olympic Gold Medals. His extraordinary talent, determination, and training regimen have inspired millions. Phelps continues to promote swimming and mental health awareness.</p>
